  <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Neutral beam heating on the TCV tokamak</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="260" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="c">2017-03-06</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The TCV tokamak contributes to physics understanding in fusion reactor research by harnessing a wide experimental tool set: in particular flexible shaping and high power electron cyclotron heating. Plasma regimes with high plasma pressure, a wider range of temperature ratios and significant fast-ion population are now attainable with a TCV heating system upgrade. In a first stage, a 1 MW neutral beam was installed (2015) and is reported in this paper.</subfield>
